data.chText: 特别的；不寻常的；罕见的
data.enText: different from what is usual or normal

data.chText: 这种树这么早开花很不寻常。
data.enText: It's unusual for the trees to flower so early.
She has a very unusual name.

data.chText: 年轻的医生每周工作70小时并不罕见。
data.enText: It's not unusual for young doctors to work a 70-hour week (= it happens often) .

data.chText: 独特的；与众不同的；别致的
data.enText: different from other similar things and therefore interesting and attractive

simple_means.memory_skill: un 不 + usual 通常的 → 异乎寻常的

example: two-career families are no longer unusual

tr: not usual or common or ordinary
being definitely out of the ordinary and unexpected
slightly odd or even a bit weird
example: a strange exaltation that was indefinable
what a strange sense of humor she has

value.def: If something is unusual, it does not happen very often or you do not see it or hear it very often.

example.ex: They have replanted many areas with rare and unusual plants...
example.tran: 他们在许多地方重新种上了珍稀植物。

example.ex: To be appreciated as a parent is quite unusual.

value.tran: 不寻常的；不常见的；罕见的

value.def: If you describe someone as unusual, you think that they are interesting and different from other people.

example.ex: He was an unusual man with great business talents.
example.tran: 此人不同凡响，具有异常敏锐的商业头脑。

value.tran: 异于常人的；与众不同的；不同凡响的

trans: 不在少数；不寻常；无异常
不平常的；极不寻常；很不寻常；非常不寻常的

partsOfSpeech.dec: ab 相反 + use 用 → 反着用 → 滥用
ab 相反 + us 用 + ive …的，abuse的形容词 → 滥用的；谩骂的
dis 不 + abuse 滥用 → 不滥用 → 纠正错误
dis 不 + use 用 → 废弃；不用
mis 坏 + use 用 → 用的不对 → 错用
un 不 + usual 通常的 → 异乎寻常的
us 用 + age 表总称 → 用法；惯例
us 用 + ual 有…性质的 → 常用的 → 通常的
ut 用 + ensil 表物品 → 用的物品 → 用具
utilit〔y〕公用事业；有用 + arian …的 → 有用为主 → 功利主义的
util 用 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 公用事业；有用
util 用 + ize 使 → 利用
